INSERT INTO `card` VALUES ('58d89302cd53f765b45d1f3f',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 12:52:57.091350','2020-06-16 23:19:40.591000','2020-09-13 12:52:57.091352',NULL,'',NULL,0,'This is a card. Drag it to the \"Tried It\" List to show it\'s done. →',564223,'https://trello.com/c/gjwfE7Ht','58d89302cd53f765b45d1f3a','58d89302cd53f765b45d1f3c'),('58d89302cd53f765b45d1f41',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 12:52:57.103045','2020-06-16 23:19:42.271000','2020-09-13 12:52:57.103046',NULL,'###Three Trello Basics: \n\n**1. Boards**: organize a project or just about anything.\n**2. Lists**: are super flexible, but often steps like *\"To Do, Doing, and Done\"*.\n**3. Cards**: represent tasks or store information. \n\n\nWatch this short video to learn more: \n\n[![](https://trello-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/571936e84bb334420cce0df1/57bdde964803b5a2d3d17f8e/9523b90931678530ec2775ebbdc124d8/this_is_a_trello_board_with_lists_and_cards.jpg)](https://trello.wistia.com/medias/n5tpbc6uo1)\n----\n\n--- \n\nYou\'re inside the *Tutorial (Start Here!)* **board** right now. \n\nYou\'re reading a **card** called *The Trello Basics*.\n\nEverything in this *Stuff to Try* **list** is a **card**. \n\nYou can add as many **lists** and **cards** to a **board** as you want.\n\n----- \n\n\n**Click** the \"X\" in the **top right corner** of this **card** to close the card and **drag it** over to the *\"Tried It\"* **list** because you\'re all done! 🎉',NULL,0,'newName',629759,'https://trello.com/c/CSucsEHb','58d89302cd53f765b45d1f3a','58d89302cd53f765b45d1f3c'),('58d89302cd53f765b45d1f49',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 12:52:57.110921','2020-06-16 23:19:41.389000','2020-09-13 12:52:57.110922','{emoji={}}','hewdfkuhjyaeshdfjuswehbdj\n','2020-06-25 02:00:00.000000',0,'Mastering Trello Cards',498687,'https://trello.com/c/gAelb0Tf','58d89302cd53f765b45d1f3a','5ee62e38546dea7d16ba88e9'),('58d89302cd53f765b45d1f53',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 12:52:57.063842','2020-06-14 00:42:48.842000','2020-09-13 12:52:57.063843','{emoji={}}','efsef\n',NULL,0,'Create Your First Board',385023,'https://trello.com/c/vP9NhPFJ','58d89302cd53f765b45d1f3a','58d89302cd53f765b45d1f3b'),('58d89302cd53f765b45d1f54',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 12:52:57.052607','2020-06-14 23:47:56.711000','2020-09-13 12:52:57.052609',NULL,'###Trello is a flexible platform for your whole [team](http://help.trello.com/article/927-what-are-teams) to collaborate and get stuff done. \n\n\n- **Power-Ups** turn Trello boards into living applications, with additional features & integrations from the apps you love! trello.com/power-ups :rocket:\n\n![](https://trello-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/57c71ac1247e638ba40f3979/600x300/0c916c343233dc8456fbe31aedbfef1d/Power-Up_Scroll_50.gif)\n\n- Bit of a tech wiz? Use our open API to build your own integrations: developers.trello.com\n\n- Also, check out these browser extensions and add-ons: trello.com/integrations',NULL,0,'Power-Ups, Integrations, APIs, oh my!',364543,'https://trello.com/c/OHZpdulj','58d89302cd53f765b45d1f3a','58d89302cd53f765b45d1f3b'),('58d89302cd53f765b45d1f5b',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 12:52:57.071744','2017-03-27 15:20:18.521000','2020-09-13 12:52:57.071745',NULL,'- Visit the **[Trello Guide](https://trello.com/guide)** to get started, get inspired, and learn more.\n\n- The **[Trello Blog](https://blog.trello.com)** has regular updates, productivity tips, and workflows. \n\n- Download Trello for **[iOS](https://itunes.apple.com/app/trello-organize-anything/id461504587)** and **[Android](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.trello)** to stay in sync when you\'re on the go. \n\n- Become a Trello productivity pro! **[Join a free webinar.](https://trello.com/webinars?utm_source=trello&utm_medium=welcome_board&utm_campaign=webinars\n)** \n\n- Questions? Visit **help.trello.com**. Or **[contact us](https://trello.com/contact)**. We\'re happy to help! 😎\n\n',NULL,0,'Help, Pro Tips, Webinars & More',393215,'https://trello.com/c/QckWQGlo','58d89302cd53f765b45d1f3a','58d89302cd53f765b45d1f3b'),('59ee4a4fdf23869858cad6d3',NULL,0,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.938145','2018-09-18 00:32:27.870000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.938146',NULL,'https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/GCI\n\nEspecially task links if we get in and start submitting tasks to the official site',NULL,0,'TODO: Update GitHub wiki GCI page for 2018',98304,'https://trello.com/c/wDG0U0RV','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b16'),('59ee7b698fa997f86e13e6a7',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.015572','2018-10-22 15:35:12.493000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.015573','{emoji={}}','After last year\'s GSoC, DestSol now supports custom factions, each with it\'s own ships and weapons. This task chain guides the student through the entire process of creating a new faction.\n\nThere are 4 basic sizes of ships in DestSol - small, medium, large and the capital (mothership). The player usually starts in a smal ship, and works his way up to large ships. The capital is reserved for the faction bases.\n\nThis task focuses on the medium ship.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Add a ship (texture, icon and config) to the game (adding them to the engine is perfectly fine, you can shift everything to your own module as part of a different task).\n* Attach a screenshot of the ship in-game as proof of your work.\n\n# Where to start\n\n* decide on the kind of faction you want (for reference, look at the existing federal and organic factions). This should help set up the theme for the textures and attributes of the ships and weapons you create.\n* TODO: Add link to wiki page describing ship creation process.\n\n# See also\n\n* Once you\'re done with this, have a look at large ship task. // TODO: Link it.',NULL,0,'Add a medium ship (I)',2273280,'https://trello.com/c/CGsbM5lQ','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb10eaaa163492c93420393'),('59ee7f07d4ae8009830d0cac',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.025525','2018-10-22 15:35:12.501000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.025526','{emoji={}}','After last year\'s GSoC, DestSol now supports custom factions, each with it\'s own ships and weapons. This task chain guides the student through the entire process of creating a new faction.\n\nThere are 4 basic sizes of ships in DestSol - small, medium, large and the capital (mothership). The player usually starts in a smal ship, and works his way up to large ships. The capital is reserved for the faction bases.\n\nThis task focuses on the large ship, and the weapons.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Add a ship (texture, icon and config) and a weapon (texture and config) to the game (adding them to the engine is perfectly fine, you can shift everything to your own module as part of a different task).\n* Attach a screenshot of the ship firing the weapon in-game as proof of your work.\n\n# Where to start\n\n* decide on the kind of faction you want (for reference, look at the existing federal and organic factions). This should help set up the theme for the textures and attributes of the ships and weapons you create.\n* TODO: Add link to wiki page describing ship creation process.\n* TODO: Add link to wiki page describing weapon creation process.\n\n# See also\n\n* If you haven\'t already completed it, check out the medium ship task. // TODO: Link it.\n* Once you\'re done with this, have a look at capital ship task. // TODO: Link it.',NULL,0,'Add a large ship along with a weapon to support it (II)',2306050,'https://trello.com/c/iytfqofC','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb10eaaa163492c93420393'),('59ee7fcb4b90ea8f4e8a8ec0',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.033731','2018-10-22 15:35:12.510000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.033732','{emoji={}}','After this year\'s GSoC, DestSol now supports custom factions, each with it\'s own ships and weapons. This task chain guides the student through the entire process of creating a new faction.\n\nThere are 4 basic sizes of ships in DestSol - small, medium, large and the capital (mothership). The player usually starts in a smal ship, and works his way up to large ships. The capital is reserved for the faction bases.\n\nThis task focuses on the capital ship, and the process of actually transferring things into a faction.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Add a ship (texture, icon and config) to the game. Note that unlike other tasks, this task requires you to create a new Module for the ship. If you have made other ships or weapons, move them to the new module as well!\n* Attach a screenshot of the ship as proof of your work, as well as a screenshot of the engine picking up your custom module.\n\n# Where to start\n\n* decide on the kind of faction you want (for reference, look at the existing federal and organic factions). This should help set up the theme for the textures and attributes of the ships and weapons you create.\n* TODO: Add link to wiki page describing ship creation process.\n* TODO: Add link to wiki page describing module creation process.\n\n# See also\n\n* If you haven\'t already completed it, check out the large ship task. // TODO: Link it.\n* Once you\'re done with this, have a look at small ship task. // TODO: Link it.',NULL,0,'Add a capital ship along with a custom module to house the ship (III)',2338820,'https://trello.com/c/nyTTQFKq','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb10eaaa163492c93420393'),('59ee80b1face1da288c3410b',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.041852','2018-10-22 15:35:12.512000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.041852','{emoji={}}','After this year\'s GSoC, DestSol now supports custom factions, each with it\'s own ships and weapons. This task chain guides the student through the entire process of creating a new faction.\n\nThere are 4 basic sizes of ships in DestSol - small, medium, large and the capital (mothership). The player usually starts in a smal ship, and works his way up to large ships. The capital is reserved for the faction bases.\n\nThis task focuses on the small ship, and making it available as a starting ship.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Add a ship (texture, icon and config) and a spawnConfig (config) to the game. The ship and spawnConfig should be added to your own Module, and not to engine.\n* Attach a screenshot of the ship in-game as proof of your work, along with a screenshot of the ship selection screen with your ship on the list.\n\n# Where to start\n\n* decide on the kind of faction you want (for reference, look at the existing federal and organic factions). This should help set up the theme for the textures and attributes of the ships and weapons you create.\n* TODO: Add link to wiki page describing ship creation process.\n* TODO: Add link to wiki page describing startingConfigs.\n\n# See also\n\n* If you haven\'t already completed it, check out the capital ship task. // TODO: Link it.',NULL,0,'Add a small ship, and make it available as the starting ship of the faction (IV)',2371580,'https://trello.com/c/i65pbhup','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb10eaaa163492c93420393'),('59eea817882fc3df3d9a24af',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.810566','2018-10-20 21:07:24.875000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.810567','{emoji={}}','_Todo for 2018:_ We have a large photo series and a few of the initial buildings done. Need to outline which buildings remain and point to where the pictures are (should be in the 2017 task in the GCI site)\n\nThis task series (estimated tasks: 20) is a build project for the Danish museum \"Hjerl Hede\" - creating textures, structure templates, and possibly block shapes in Blender to replicate a set of buildings one at a time\n\nEach task will have as a goal to make a Structural Template (ST) definition for a given building, including needed textures and possibly shapes for unique blocks (like blocks making up a water wheel, or an outright 3d water wheel object).\n\nThe purpose of the overall task series is to get a set of related buildings that could be used to create the museum grounds in-game as well as having more general purpose building templates\n\nIt also serves as an introduction to coordinating team efforts (all PRs to the same GitHub repo) and testing a unified project - the module will be auto-deployed on a server so the participating students can place STs together in a growing village\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Pull Request submitted to the target repo (TODO: Create) containing all assets and config to place one specific building in-world\n* One or more screenshots showing the building placed repeatedly in-world (not the original used to create the ST - several placed using an ST tool)\n\n# Where to start\n\n* See https://github.com/Terasology/StructureTemplates for general guidance about the ST system and http://forum.terasology.org/threads/structure-templates.1550/for more on the topic\n* See https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/GCI#Artwork- TODO: Create - where did our general texturing/license page go?\n* Review provided images & links to study the target building to determine what textures and blocks are needed\n\n# See also\n\n* Suggested prerequisite: ST task chain step 1\n* Suggested follow-up: ST task chain Ultimate (entire \"culture\" including village generation)\n* http://hjerlhede.dk - museum website\n\n# Tags\n\n(These get entered separately on the GCI site, so they don\'t count toward the body character count limit)\n\n* Building\n* Design\n* 2D texturing\n* Blender\n* 3D shapes\n* JSON\n* Testing',NULL,0,'20x Build series: Hjerl Hede museum',1740800,'https://trello.com/c/wUTMq9rI','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b19'),('59eeb558da586e215c9c0c58',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.165348','2018-10-23 00:43:56.070000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.165349','{emoji={}}','Not every piece of code is self-documenting :) To help explain what our code does, Terasology uses Javadoc - a system of documentation that uses structured inline comments - and provides guidelines for well-formed documentation. Your task is to find a method or class in the Terasology engine or any module where Javadoc is missing and add it!\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* A pull request containing new Javadoc documentation is submitted to the engine or any module repo. At least 5 easy classes (small components and interfaces) or one harder class (a system or widget) should be documented.\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Prepare your workspace (task) or even run the game from source before starting! \n* [Look for interesting modules](http://github.com/Terasology) and [use `groovyw get module <name>` to get the source code to your workspace](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/Developing-Modules#fetch-an-existing-module). Take your time to understand what the code does, then write some Javadoc :)\n* Ask mentors on IRC if you\'re not quite sure how some code works or where to find lots of undocumented code to dig through\n\n# See also\n\n* [The GCI page of documentation for general info](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/GCI#documentation--training)\n\n**Note**: This is a multi-instance task and other students may claim it as well, they might even end up trying to document the same thing. Please look on GitHub in the target repo for any pending PRs that may already cover code you were interested in documenting.',NULL,0,'JavaDoc: Find something undocumented, then document it',16384,'https://trello.com/c/5mOP1IZD','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb13feff9698564f44ccc4b'),('59eeb7fc4db5dbcca370e274',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.295522','2018-10-23 16:52:53.147000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.295523',NULL,'We use test plans for manually verifying that things work as expected. See https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/GCI#test-plans for details.\n\nThis task is for validating the Rails module using the existing test plan at https://github.com/Terasology/Rails/wiki/Rails-Test-Plan - note that Rails went over a refactoring since the test plan was written so some parts may be broken and new stuff may be available to test\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Student should provide a step-by-step review notes including screenshots for testing the Rails module. This should be provided in a separate document (not a task comment!) like a GitHub Gist or forum thread\n* If any steps fail include details for the failure and review the issue with a mentor before submitting the task (get guidance on whether it is a test plan failure or a misunderstanding)\n* Any improvements to the test plan have been edited into the wiki page\n\n# Where to start\n\n* See https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/GCI#test-plans to learn more about test plans\n* Download the game at https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/releases or use the game launcher\n* Run the game with the Rails module active and step through the test plan, taking notes!\n\n# See also\n\n* Other tasks involving test plans, either reviewing existing ones or writing new ones\n\n# Tags\n\n(These get entered separately on the GCI site, so they don\'t count toward the body character count limit)\n\n* Testing\n* Documentation\n* Validation\n* Rails\n* Trains',NULL,0,'Test plan: Rails module, go through and test, update if needed',1777660,'https://trello.com/c/AQ98fTCD','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb13ffda245836ef12b392c'),('59eeb8b80603c70e6c5f64e9',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.303898','2018-10-23 16:55:18.623000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.303898','{emoji={}}','We use test plans for manually verifying that things work as expected. See https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/GCI#test-plans for details.\n\nThis task is for validating the Potions module using the existing test plan at https://github.com/Terasology/Potions/wiki/Test-Plan - note that potions tend to be tricky and break somewhat regularly so this may need a lot of confirmation from a mentor whether something is truly broken or just hard to test\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Student should provide a step-by-step review notes including screenshots for testing the Rails module. This should be provided in a separate document (not a task comment!) like a GitHub Gist or forum thread\n* If any steps fail include details for the failure and review the issue with a mentor before submitting the task (get guidance on whether it is a test plan failure or a misunderstanding)\n* Any improvements to the test plan have been edited into the wiki page\n\n# Where to start\n\n* See https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/GCI#test-plans to learn more about test plans\n* Download the game at https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/releases or use the game launcher\n* Run the game with the Potions module active and step through the test plan, taking notes!\n\n# See also\n\n* Other tasks involving test plans, either reviewing existing ones or writing new ones',NULL,0,'Test plan: Potions module, go through and test, update if needed',1843200,'https://trello.com/c/CNETAlBS','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb13ffda245836ef12b392c'),('59eebbda767ba36eb8b83780',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.352048','2018-10-22 15:35:37.335000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.352049','{emoji={}}','As a prerequisite you should first do the task to set up a developer workspace for yourself. Then this task can be paired with another student performing the developer workstation setup with you guiding them and gathering notes on how well they did and if the setup instructions could be improved.\n\nNote that ideally your friend should actually be able to use the help - no fair if you try to \"help\" an IT professional set up to run from source! ;-)\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Student should provide a small report of how their friend managed to set up to run from source and which problems were encountered, if any, with improvements to the documentation suggested (use a GitHub Gist or a forum thread)\n* Provide a screen from your friend\'s computer showing the game running from source at the same time some chat from you is visible (like a running chat log from IRC or some instant messenger)\n* Bonus: Have either/both of you provide a minimal new game asset in a PR as well\n\n# Where to start\n\n* See https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/Dev-Setup for instructions - although you should have already gone through those!\n* See https://github.com/Terasology/TutorialAssetSystem/wiki for basic asset work (other tasks also available there)\n\n# See also\n\n* Prerequisite: The dev setup / workspace task\n* Suggested follow-up: help a friend test a feature in multiplayer',NULL,0,'Introduce a friend to running the game from source and adding a simple new piece of content',344064,'https://trello.com/c/B5plkpua','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb1400605e0cc6f01a9e124'),('59ef5c5b77e54a2b00ae7977',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.340628','2018-10-22 15:35:37.295000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.340629','{emoji={}}','TODO: Make a next step task that includes the https://forum.terasology.org/threads/facadeserver-headless-server-with-web-interface.1906/\n\nOne of the biggest features of Terasology is the multiplayer aspect of the game. As part of this task, we would like the students to set up a multiplayer server, play around in it with their friends and report back any issues they encounter or suggestions they have.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Student should provide step-by-step review notes including screenshots of the game showing other people in-game. This should be provided in a separate document (not a task comment!) like a GitHub Gist or forum thread\n* If any steps fail include details for the failure and review the issue with a mentor before submitting the task (get guidance on whether it is a Terasology issue or an issue of misconfiguration)\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Download the game launcher - https://github.com/MovingBlocks/TerasologyLauncher/releases\n* Start a new server with a few fun mods enabled, and go bananas!\n\n# See also\n\n* If you haven\'t already, check out \"Help a friend build from source\" before this task.',NULL,0,'Set up a game server, write feedback on usability',278528,'https://trello.com/c/PCYbC38W','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb1400605e0cc6f01a9e124'),('59ef5c713a5f6ac3f9e6a353',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.216478','2018-10-22 15:35:37.299000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.216479','{emoji={}}','#Review wiki pages\nEvery open source project needs documentation - tons and tons of it. However, with time the documentation might become obsolete, and even the documentation that isn\'t obsolete can always use some love.\n\nThis task requires the students to go through the wiki, fixing broken links or better expressing a particular section.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Make a new page with the \"gciDraft\" suffix, and make all the relevant changes to that page.\n* Screenshots highlighting the changes made to the page.\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Check out the wiki\'s for modules by going to a repo on [this list](https://github.com/Terasology) and then going to the wiki tab\n    * Not all modules have wikis, if the module you open doesn\'t have one then just pick a different module.\n* [The main Terasology wiki](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki)\n* [The main Destination Sol wiki](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/DestinationSol/wiki)\n\n# See also\n\n* Other tasks related to documentation, like \"flesh out NUI wiki\".',NULL,0,'Review wiki pages',278528,'https://trello.com/c/gsnphwJv','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb13feff9698564f44ccc4b'),('59ef5f40a528e1919364fedd',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.278885','2018-10-22 15:35:16.278000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.278885','{emoji={}}','#Run the game with a profiler to find something bad\nTerasology\'s core developers regularly use profiling tools to measure game performance: random lag or inconsistent performance over long periods of time can be a sign of a badly optimized system, and memory usage constantly going up over time can only mean that a memory leak\'s managed to sneak in. \n\nYour task is to test the performance of the running game with some set of modules enabled that end up causing a game slowdown. Look at the profiler data, take some screenshots, and propose a theory as to what\'s wrong and what may help.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* You\'ve managed to run the game with the YourKit profiler enabled - take one or more screenshots of a case in which it looks like something is problematic with performance (some operation takes a while and is heavily tied up in one or two specific areas)\n* Provide a small write-up with a theory as to why and how the problem may be resolved (as a GitHub Gist/issue or forum post)\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Firstly you should pick which profiler you want to use. We recommend either java\'s FlightRecorder or YourKit.\n  * If you pick Flight Recorder then [use the default run profile](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/pull/3475)\n  * If you use [YourKit then download it](https://yourkit.com/java/profiler/download) using the 15 day free trial\n  * Read some docs or watch some demos - https://yourkit.com/docs (YouTube would probably also be good)\n  * Get YourKit hooked up with IntelliJ running Terasology \n* Try out the JoshariasSurvival gameplay template - there are known memory leaks somewhere in there',NULL,0,'Run the game with a profiler to find something bad',622592,'https://trello.com/c/VPygGwkN','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb13ffda245836ef12b392c'),('59efb4085a6b13da522244da',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.128227','2018-10-22 15:35:37.266000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.128228','{emoji={}}','One of the oddities missing from our in-house UI framework is support for tabbing between components, and a notion of tab order values being assigned to UI components somehow.\n\nThis task is meant to implement such a tab ordering system.\n\nThe concept of order between components might need to be introduced, or maybe some sort of existing depth value could be reused. Components need to be able to have their tab order set explicitly, but by default should likely increment up based on the order in which the components are added. Some components (like labels) should be opted out of the tabbing order.\n\nThis may not be a super easy task so make sure you\'ve done several other UI tasks before attempting this one.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* A PR is submitted to the engine repository adding tabbing support to NUI components. This should include sensible defaults for existing components.\n* Include a series of screenshots, a gif, or a small video showing you tabbing between different elements, seeing the focus move along different buttons.\n\n# Where to start\n\n* [The tutorial for the UI system](https://github.com/Terasology/TutorialNUI)\n* Other UI tasks\n\n# See also\n\n* [The GCI guide on UI](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/GCI#user-interface)\n* [The primary issue for this task](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/issues/483)',NULL,0,'Add tab order to NUI',2076670,'https://trello.com/c/JLXHGy0a','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb13fe396623c2292321640'),('59f24fc7418df6035da0b697',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.483416','2018-10-01 01:49:59.608000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.483417','{emoji={}}','Cards in this list should use the \"Card Repeater\" Trello powerup, much like https://trello.com/b/E6PfiSX8/roles-and-projects board will when we start using it seriously. The idea is to make cards that spawn new instances on a regular basis into a second list, that\'ll then show a growing backlog of things needing work.\n\nFor GCI let us try doing this just for having people commit to making new tasks every x days so we can have plenty by the time the program opens ;-)\n\nSo! If you volunteer to make at least 1 task every x days simply add a card here saying so, assign yourself, and enable the Repeater, setting it accordingly to when you think you can add a task. If you miss one or two that\'s fine, you\'ll just have to catch up when you can :D\n\nSuggestion: Make a copy of the template card to use as your repeater card.  That way you can edit the card the repeater created to craft the task, then move it over into a different list to park the prepared task. Or if you create a task directly in the GCI site move the card into the \"Tasks moved to GCI site\" list',NULL,0,'What is this?',16384,'https://trello.com/c/vJfRoR5X','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b1d'),('59f294e436cf489c939d06ad',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.946413','2018-09-14 12:59:33.793000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.946414',NULL,'Since that effort does much the same thing: try to make a project more welcoming to new contributors. https://github.com/blog/2452-get-started-with-hacktoberfest',NULL,0,'Review some good practices from Hacktoberfest?',114688,'https://trello.com/c/KLnP1LRf','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b16'),('59f89e063f4410abebb99c31',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.852942','2018-10-01 09:01:11.856000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.852942',NULL,'TeraMath is a math library that is written for Terasology. Vector project is a function of projecting a vector U onto V. Write some test vectors that show that vector project is working correctly.\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vector_projection\n\n\n![vector](https://trello-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/59ee428ff5d7da7d752ab669/59f89e063f4410abebb99c31/7ff4400e6f8f0c883c0ed0b61e552bbb/vector.png)\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* A functioning unit test that shows the project function works correctly\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Look at the project function: https://github.com/pollend/TeraMath/blob/a315cca94a0a26a26100d002eecd98047bbe1af7/src/generator/resources/BaseVector.st#L96\n\n* Example test can be found under TeraMath/src/test/java/org/terasology/math/geom/ \n\n* Write a test for each use case of project under:\n - ImmutableVector2dTest.java\n - ImmutableVector3dTest.java\n - Vector2dTest.java\n - Vector3dTest.java\n\n# See also\n\n* TODO: link to how to write unit test\n* \n\n# Tags\n\n* UnitTest',NULL,0,'UnitTest: TeraMath Project',319488,'https://trello.com/c/KI96emVg','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b12cc027ee465284c3254'),('59f89e1ffefa82f1077e869a',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.240655','2018-10-22 15:35:16.215000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.240656','{emoji={}}','Every project loves unit tests, but few have enough!\n\nOur engine has nearly 700 tests, which is nowhere near enough, yet modules often have none at all.\n\nYour task is to find a module without tests (or with very few), containing logic that *can* be tested, then adding some tests (5+) to validate some / all of the logic.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* A PR is submitted to a module repo containing new tests for any module repo with code to unit test.\n* Include a screenshot of successful test output or copy the output\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Read http://forum.terasology.org/threads/tutorial-unit-testing-intensifies.1878/ for an introduction to unit testing and the general philosophy of why\n* See some of the unit tests in the engine (http://jenkins.terasology.org/job/Terasology/lastCompletedBuild/testReport/) or or the few modules that do have unit tests (like the NameGenerator or MarkovChains) for inspiration\n* Look for a module with code in it that is lacking tests - see https://github.com/Terasology and look for a `src/main/test` path - that\'s where tests would exist\n\n# See also\n\n* https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/GCI#quality-assurance for some general stuff on testing',NULL,0,'Unit testing: Add tests to an existing module',32768,'https://trello.com/c/maVq3aqf','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb13ffda245836ef12b392c'),('5a008715d41fea7451962864',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.996608','2018-10-23 00:43:55.826000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.996609','{emoji={}}','# Create a Unique Cart\n\nRails is a module that adds carts and rails to Terasology. This module at the moment has a base cart and base rail segment and a flip-able T junction. We would like to expand on this and add a variety of both new rail segments and carts to the AdditionalRails Module.\n\nFeel free to make the assets temporary in the sense that its ok to reuse the carts from the base module. Make sure to make them distinguishable from the default  to avoid confusion. The carts themselves can be reworked in the future. \n\nThe one example that comes with Additional Rails module is locomotive cart. Basically this is a self powered cart that can push things. joining carts is not possible at the moment. The cart does not need to be really creative to be a contribution. Generally the more mundane the better. \n\nThis tasks focuses on adding a new carts to Terasology.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Demonstrate that the additional rail/cart is working as intended.\n * Show a screenshot of the finished cart but a video would be preferable\n* Create a pull request on the [AdditionalRails](https://github.com/Terasology/AdditionalRails) Repository\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Look at the example [locomotive](https://github.com/Terasology/AdditionalRails/blob/master/src/main/java/org/terasology/additionalRails/action/LocomotiveAction.java) that comes with the AdditionalRails module.\n* More Details about the base implementation are found in the [Rails module](https://github.com/Terasology/Rails\n)\n * Look at the base cart that comes with Rails\n\n# See also\n* [Task to Research new Rail/Cart](https://codein.withgoogle.com/dashboard/tasks/5165141185265664/)\n* [Task to Create a Unique Rail](https://codein.withgoogle.com/dashboard/tasks/4555414944350208/)',NULL,0,'Create a Unique Cart',849920,'https://trello.com/c/TI679duN','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb10eaaa163492c93420393'),('5a047ba7d4692dd95ea37b16',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.988744','2018-10-22 15:35:37.370000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.988745','{emoji={}}','#Create a Unique Rail\n\nRails is a module that adds carts and rails to Terasology. This module at the moment has a base cart and base rail segment and a flip-able T junction. We would like to expand on this and add a variety of both new rail segments and carts to the AdditionalRails Module.\n\nFeel free to make the assets temporary in the sense that its ok to reuse the carts from the base module and base rail segments. Make sure to make them distinguishable from the default  to avoid confusion. \n\nAdditional Rails module comes with a booster rail. Basically the booster rail will add acceleration to a cart up to some fixed velocity. This is fairly simple but its possible to add more complex rail segments. \n\nThe new addition does not necessarily really need to involve a new track segment.  The T junction at the moment can be switched with the wrench. Using some kind of switch block next to one of these tracks that switches the  with the signalling module would be of interest. Basically this would allow some basic automation of switching using signalling. More mundane block such as a track segment that slows down a cart would also be good. \n\nThis tasks focuses on adding new rail block to Terasology. Feel free to incorporate other modules.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Demonstrate that the additional rail/cart is working as intended.\n * Show a screenshot of the finished cart but a video would be preferable\n* Create a pull request on the AdditionalRails Repository\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Look at the [booster rail](https://github.com/Terasology/AdditionalRails/blob/master/src/main/java/org/terasology/additionalRails/action/BoosterAction.java) block that comes with the module\n\n* More Details about the base implementation are found in the Segmented Paths module.\n\n# See also\n\nhttps://github.com/Terasology/Rails\nhttps://github.com/Terasology/AdditionalRails',NULL,0,'Create a Unique Rail',647168,'https://trello.com/c/LbdjOhVh','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb10eaaa163492c93420393'),('5a071ebe0f9119e7ea623c04',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.320605','2018-10-22 15:35:37.326000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.320606','{emoji={}}','# Research New Rail/Cart\nRails is a module that adds carts and rails to Terasology. At the moment we only have a handful of carts and a few rails.  \nWe would like to expand on this and add a variety of both new rail segments and carts to the Additional Rails Module.\n\nThis task involves researching and designing a new cart or rail to be added to the module. This cart can use functionality from other modules, like the Planting and Harvesting carts which use features from Simple Farming.\n\n*We will not accept submissions with only a few sentences. Please be detailed.*\n\n# Definition of Done\n* A [GitHub Gist](https://gist.github.com/) with a detailed description of the new cart/rail\n\n# Where to start\n* Take a look at [all the existing Terasology repos](http://github.com/Terasology)\n* Have a look at [existing carts in Additional Rails](https://github.com/Terasology/AdditionalRails)\n\n# See Also\n* One other Rails task\n* Follow up task to implement a new cart design',NULL,0,'Research new Rail/Cart',49152,'https://trello.com/c/ltMjTc3D','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb1400605e0cc6f01a9e124'),('5b9b1054ebb7938b3b80e1c6',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.896204','2018-09-18 00:35:02.498000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.896206','{emoji={}}','Welcome to our task staging board for [GCI 2018](https://codein.withgoogle.com/about/)!\n\nWe\'ll be developing tasks here before entering them into the GCI system, keeping some back to have a reserve for later in the work period.\n\n## Task Types\n\nLabels are used to mark the type (not category, that\'s the column) of a task.\n\n* Multi-instance - this task will be entered with `x` available copies of the same base task. Either students can do the same thing over and over (setting up their own source code workspace) or there is enough ground to cover for multiple students (adding javadoc to various places). In some cases the instance count will be increased over the work period\n* Task Chain - this task is part of a multi-step chain where it is expected a student will go step-by-step in order (most if not always these tasks will also be multi-instance). Traditionally these have been very popular\n* Task Series - this task is one card in Trello but will be written out into multiple tasks on the GCI site that are closely related yet unique. Use \"`#` x\" in the card title to indicate roughly how many tasks are expected\n* Advanced - for the rare excelling student looking for something more challenging. These tasks should caution to students that they are of above average difficulty and unless comfortable with the topic work some more normal tasks first\n\n## Task areas\n\nLabels are also used to indicate the target project as we have multiple areas to write tasks about: our primary projects and some sub-projects or even umbrella projects.\n\n* Terasology tasks: primary and likely a majority of the tasks. Lots of things to screenshot in-game, write-up on GitHub or in our forum, and discuss on our IRC\n* Destination Sol tasks: secondary project as we\'ve matured it to where it is easier to code on and add new content like spaceships to\n* Tertiary tools and other smaller projects: We have a few other projects like the Box2D editor for DestSol and a growing collection of utilities to work on, we may be able to make some tasks out of those as well\n* Tiled - should we consider being an umbrella corp again for Tiled or anybody else?\n\n## Self Challenging Tasks\n\nFor volunteers eager to help make tasks: Challenge yourself to write 1 task every x days over in \"Volunteer Task Maker\" list (enable the \"Repeater\" addon) then use the cards that generate as a draft for a new task.\n\n## Archives\n\nLook at https://codein.withgoogle.com/archive/2016/organization/5742351410528256/task/ or https://codein.withgoogle.com/archive/2017/organization/5750501782061056/task/ for tasks from past years, plenty of those (especially multi-instance) should still be workable as new tasks for this year',NULL,0,'Please read me for info :-)',16384,'https://trello.com/c/dlupyclk','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b16'),('5b9b1060e173eb29dc81890a',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.904894','2018-10-21 23:09:12.606000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.904895','{emoji={}}','# Title (card name)\n\nIntro text - describe the involved stuff (code, component, website, document, etc) briefly, what\'s missing, and what\'s desired\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Put bullet points here for the final state that\'ll satisfy the task\n* Include at least one \"deliverable\" - usually a screenshot for any task involving game assets (forces testing of the game - if it doesn\'t work yet then the task isn\'t done yet, ask for help!), a forum thread or wiki page for a document, a youtube link for a video, and so on\n\n# Where to start\n\n* More bullet points! Give the student instructions for the starting state to aim for (working workspace etc)\n* Give names of classes or other code resources to search for, if applicable\n* Link to related information to investigate\n\n# See also\n\n* Put a link here to a section on https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/GCI if there is one describing this specific category of task\n* Any other information that may be relevant, such as suggested tasks to consider before or after this task',NULL,0,'Task template',32768,'https://trello.com/c/hfwnyYYu','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b16'),('5b9b108266824a3226f0ac12',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.914301','2018-09-19 02:49:18.294000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.914303','{emoji={}}','General notes for good areas to write Terasology tasks for \n\n* Videos - we should probably put a section on the GCI wiki page for how to best make a video, including the little teaser/prefix clip we use for Terasology videos?\n* Rail related tasks - Skysom & mpollend ?\n* GooKeeper - new creatures, blocks, etc\n* MasterOfOreon - new buildings, tasks, Oreon types, etc\n* GooeyDefence - new tower pieces, new enemies\n* KComputer - new peripherals?\n* Light & Shadow - new weapons / mechanics, help finish MVP? Trickier\n* Event recording - prepare new tests\n* Server facade - mix it into the task(s) for experimenting with the game and writing feedback?',NULL,0,'Terasology idea areas',49152,'https://trello.com/c/Jba40Lqy','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b16'),('5b9b108ae23e8c816c6a42f6',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.924498','2018-09-15 00:17:47.285000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.924499',NULL,'TODO: General notes for good areas to write tasks for here',NULL,0,'Destination Sol idea areas',65536,'https://trello.com/c/1dcyO6bw','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b16'),('5b9b1095f802330d04a60140',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.931291','2018-09-15 00:17:52.545000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.931291',NULL,'TODO: General notes for good areas to write tasks for here\n\n(Example sub projects: Box2D editor for DestSol, Hubot/Probot stuff, etc)',NULL,0,'Misc sub-project idea areas',81920,'https://trello.com/c/kYI1fzDR','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b16'),('5b9b14f26f716e4f380083cf',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.312286','2018-10-23 16:58:49.353000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.312287',NULL,'Beyond manual testing, writing test plans, and basic unit testing there are more advanced sorts of testing that can be done with the help of tools. Terasology has a game environment testing class called the ModuleTestingEnvironment (MTE) that can start a headless game server, connect clients to it, and simulate activities that can then be validated against.\n\nYour task is to use this class to validate some activity from a module. The existing (and new during this GCI) test plan write-ups are ideal material for this task, and automating a full one would be amazing!\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* A PR is submitted to a module repo with a MTE test suite exercising some of the module\n* Take a screenshot or copy paste a successful execution of the MTE test suite to include\n\n# Where to start\n\n* See the MTE instructions at https://github.com/Terasology/ModuleTestingEnvironment and its forum thread at http://forum.terasology.org/threads/moduletestingenvironment-integration-testing-with-in-process-engine-objects.1884\n* Read one or more of the test plans, try following them manually in-game, review the code they\'re exercising, then use the MTE to cause each step of what you previously did manually in the game client\n\n# See also\n\n* The test plan tasks - you can do one of those first then write an MTE test suite to validate each step in the test plan \n* The various other unit test related tasks (doing those first as well could be helpful)\n\n\n# Tags\n\n(These get entered separately on the GCI site, so they don\'t count toward the body character count limit)\n\n* Testing\n* Integration Testing\n* Automation\n* Logistics',NULL,0,'Advanced Integration Testing - validate a thing in-game automatically',1908740,'https://trello.com/c/g4kcKtbw','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb13ffda245836ef12b392c'),('5b9b217dd55c268376365e8d',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.607872','2019-10-17 01:05:07.402000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.607874','{emoji={}}','Initial setup task certainly is multi-instance, maybe including a silly throwaway plugin. Past that maybe this is more of a unique task for specific things we need',NULL,0,'Chat bot (difficulty: infrastructure, permissions, testing)',65535,'https://trello.com/c/XNsRk2Zl','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b18'),('5b9b2195b1d4644d7e999fc7',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.627562','2018-09-14 12:58:13.764000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.627563','{emoji={}}','Chain potential: \n\n* Make a simple behavior and show that it works\n* Apply the behavior to some actual gameplay content (comes close to Master of Oreon\'s task potential)\n* Validate the behavior using automated testing (MTE, event recording?)\n\n*Note:* In the past we had a task to write out *designs* for behaviors that would then be implemented. There are still a bunch of them in the forum we could link from here, and we could do the task again (just ask to be distinct from existing write-ups)',NULL,0,'Behavior tree AI (difficulty: tricky subject, fairly deep to mentor)',131071,'https://trello.com/c/9mPscZTm','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b18'),('5b9bf5441eb0c68a7759ff50',NULL,0,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.863723','2018-09-15 03:52:50.753000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.863726','{emoji={}}','Title (card name)\nIntro text - describe the involved stuff (code, component, website, document, etc) briefly, what\'s missing, and what\'s desired\n\nDefinition of \'Done\'\nPut bullet points here for the final state that\'ll satisfy the task\nInclude at least one \"deliverable\" - usually a screenshot for any task involving game assets (forces testing of the game - if it doesn\'t work yet then the task isn\'t done yet, ask for help!), a forum thread or wiki page for a document, a youtube link for a video, and so on\nWhere to start\nMore bullet points! Give the student instructions for the starting state to aim for (working workspace etc)\nGive names of classes or other code resources to search for, if applicable\nLink to related information to investigate\nSee also\nPut a link here to a section on https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/GCI if there is one describing this specific category of task\nAny other information that may be relevant, such as suggested tasks to consider before or after this task\nTags\n(These get entered separately on the GCI site, so they don\'t count toward the body character count limit)\n\nTag 1\nTag 2\nTag 3 ...',NULL,0,'Replay Test: Damage taken after a fall',1581060,'https://trello.com/c/2OjtUFPu','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b12cc027ee465284c3254'),('5b9bf5841eb0c68a775a0c9e',NULL,0,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.874244','2018-09-15 03:53:28.867000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.874245',NULL,'# Title (card name)\n\nIntro text - describe the involved stuff (code, component, website, document, etc) briefly, what\'s missing, and what\'s desired\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Put bullet points here for the final state that\'ll satisfy the task\n* Include at least one \"deliverable\" - usually a screenshot for any task involving game assets (forces testing of the game - if it doesn\'t work yet then the task isn\'t done yet, ask for help!), a forum thread or wiki page for a document, a youtube link for a video, and so on\n\n# Where to start\n\n* More bullet points! Give the student instructions for the starting state to aim for (working workspace etc)\n* Give names of classes or other code resources to search for, if applicable\n* Link to related information to investigate\n\n# See also\n\n* Put a link here to a section on https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/GCI if there is one describing this specific category of task\n* Any other information that may be relevant, such as suggested tasks to consider before or after this task\n\n# Tags\n\n(These get entered separately on the GCI site, so they don\'t count toward the body character count limit)\n\n* Tag 1\n* Tag 2\n* Tag 3 ...',NULL,0,'Task template 2',1581060,'https://trello.com/c/nZlz0VOU','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b12cc027ee465284c3254'),('5b9bf6084be8de784ba1be97',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.232693','2018-10-22 15:35:16.188000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.232694','{emoji={}}','# Replay Test: Damage taken after fall\n\nWith the new Record and Replay (R&R) feature we can now record a game using the Core module and then use that as a test.\n\nThis task is to use R&R as well as `TestReplayModule` to test falling off something high and then to test that the player takes fall damage.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* A Replay Test that executes a replay that the player takes fall damage and then asserts the damage.\n* A video showing the replay running on the headed test environment and the assert passing.\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Get `TestReplayModule` on your workspace. [Instructions on how to fetch a module](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/Developing-Modules)\n* [Read about Replay Tests on the wiki](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/Replay-Tests)\n* [Check the example test code](https://github.com/Terasology/TestReplayModule/blob/master/src/test/java/org/terasology/replayTests/examples/ExampleAcceptanceTest.java) to understand how to get the `LocalPlayer` from the game.\n* Get the necessary data for the test from the `LocalPlayer` or `CoreRegistry`\n\n# See also\n\n* [The Record and Replay Wiki](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/How-to-Use-Record-and-Replay)',NULL,0,'Replay Test: Damage taken after fall',24576,'https://trello.com/c/PejrPZfd','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb13ffda245836ef12b392c'),('5b9e868de8f242483df5454d',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.174735','2018-10-22 15:35:37.259000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.174736','{emoji={}}','# Updated training video for dev setup\n\nOnce in a while somebody will prepare a video showing them setting up to run Terasology from source then proceed to develop something minor to demonstrate. But these videos go out of date as the project changes.\n\nThe goal of this task is to make a new one showcasing the very latest code and utility, such as using the `groovyw` script to fetch and update modules.\n\nAlternatively this could also be done for Destination Sol or some of our tool projects (the Box2D Editor, Kallisti + JNLua, etc)\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* A video is submitted online in a public video sharing site - likely Youtube, but Vimeo would also work\n* The video should show the process from start to finish (cloning the code to the game running from source)\n* Include a few new elements like how to use the `groovyw` script and some new modules of interest like the ModuleTestingEnvironment or TestReplayModule\n\n# Where to start\n\n* See some older example videos like https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m2t5Xl0Zxos or https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cCMQ5VaKnfw or even [this blog guide by Nihal](https://nihal111.github.io/2016/11/22/Terasology-Getting-started.html)\n* Review the Terasology dev docs, such as https://metaterasology.github.io/docs/developerIntro/fullWorkspace.html\n* Consider searching Google for tips and tricks to make nice and engaging instructional videos. For instance you can use text-based annotation instead of voice instructions (those can be edited over time and translate easier)\n\n# See also\n\n* Put a link here to a section on https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/GCI if there is one describing this specific category of task\n* Any other information that may be relevant, such as suggested tasks to consider before or after this task',NULL,0,'Updated training video for dev setup',32768,'https://trello.com/c/1g56umm3','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb13feff9698564f44ccc4b'),('5b9e8a5ec0504c1d6e02ab4e',NULL,0,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.720205','2018-09-24 12:51:54.183000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.720206',NULL,'',NULL,0,'Add a custom model for a block or entity',2043900,'https://trello.com/c/g0R2L8Sj','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b18'),('5b9e8c61f13cc833b4f6926a',NULL,0,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.648377','2018-09-18 00:02:54.703000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.648379',NULL,'',NULL,0,'use the blender exporter',278527,'https://trello.com/c/ddI8JDPb','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b18'),('5b9ea2c7734f9d423e86a97b',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.082913','2018-10-22 15:35:37.202000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.082914','{emoji={}}','# Add a screen to name a recording\n\nAt the moment when the user saves a recording it defaults to the name of the world. This can lead to older recordings being overwritten.\n\nIf there is already a recording with the same name then a screen should be shown asking the user to either re-name the recording or overwrite the existing recording.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Creation of a new file `.ui` that consists of a screen asking for the recording\'s name.\n* The screen triggers when a recording of the same name already exists.\n* [A new PR to the engine with the above changes](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology)\n\n# Where to start\n\n* [Check the UI Tutorial for how to make a new screen](https://github.com/Terasology/TutorialNui/wiki/Quick-Start)\n* [Check out some existing ui files for examples](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/tree/develop/engine/src/main/resources/assets/ui)\n\n# See also\n\n* [The issue this task is based off](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/issues/3465)',NULL,0,'Add a screen to name a recording',1667070,'https://trello.com/c/dvFLKUjF','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb13fe396623c2292321640'),('5b9ec386fd71a075d05b1c8d',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.829542','2018-09-18 00:15:40.849000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.829545','{emoji={}}','# Write wiki page for Destination Sol\n\nOur secondary game, Destination Sol, has recently gone through some changes, which are not yet reflected in the project\'s wiki. More importantly, though, lots of guides useful for content creation has so far not been written at all. Thus, your task will be to write one of those pages, so other contributors can then use them to create interesting new content!\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* A new wiki page for one of the topics in [this issue](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/DestinationSol/issues/218) is written.\n* Once done, supply a link to the task in here.\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Familiarize yourself with the concepts used during new content creation\n* See https://help.github.com/articles/about-github-wikis/ to find out what github wiki is and how to work with it\n* Pop-in to our chat to ask for help if you need so! (https://forum.terasology.org/pages/chat/)\n\n# See also\n\n* TODO put links to creating new ships tasks\n\n# Tags\n\n* Documentation\n* Tag 2\n* Tag 3 ...',NULL,0,'5x Write wiki page for Destination Sol',49152,'https://trello.com/c/gH3V0hyG','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b12a5484539133a006dc9'),('5b9ee9bb1711791180e51817',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.091308','2018-10-23 04:08:41.517000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.091308','{emoji={}}','# Improve Record and Replay UI\n\nThe Record and Replay feature needs some UI changes since its addition resulted in the addition of two buttons to the Main Menu. Those buttons should go somewhere else to make the Main Menu cleaner, see the issue for some suggestions of other places to put them.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n**Please get your design approved by a mentor before making the PR**\n\n* The change to the ui should be made in [a PR to the main engine](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology)\n\n# Where to start\n\n* [Check the UI Tutorial for how to make a new screen](https://github.com/Terasology/TutorialNui/wiki/Quick-Start)\n* [Check out some existing ui files for examples](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/tree/develop/engine/src/main/resources/assets/ui)',NULL,0,'Improve Record and Replay UI',1732610,'https://trello.com/c/jBaFyEBb','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb13fe396623c2292321640'),('5b9ef572ade870751753ea28',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.839265','2018-09-21 02:56:03.252000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.839267','{emoji={}}','# Title (card name)\n\nTerasology uses an [entity system](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Entity%E2%80%93component%E2%80%93system) for just about everything, and our goal is to apply the same library to Destination Sol. While we have a decent amount of documentation on it we don\'t have one of our typical tutorials-in-a-repo yet. This task includes creating the very basics of such a tutorial!\n\n.. times 3, as we really need this for the basic ES intro, then one focused around events and interactions, and finally one for how to annotate your stuff right for multiplayer. So this card could probably split into 3 separate pseudo-chains each building its own tutorial.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* A new module repo named \"TutorialEntitySystem\" (and \"TutorialEventsInteractions\", and \"TutorialMultiplayerExtras\") is created on GitHub with some sample code that works and at least one chapter in its wiki explaining the sample code\n* Include at least one screenshot in the wiki showing the example functioning\n\n# Where to start\n\n* We have several wiki pages already existing on the topic, such as [this one](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/Entity-System-Architecture) or others listed in the original issue\n* Look at other tutorials like the [world generation tutorial](https://github.com/Terasology/TutorialWorldGeneration/) to see how a tutorial wiki and the associated sample code is lined out\n* Create a new tutorial module locally and make something super simple work! It can be as little as an `UpdateSubscriberSystem` printing a log statement once a second or a block you can `e` click to cause an action\n\n# See also\n\n* https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/issues/2153 - the original issue requesting this tutorial\n* https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/issues/2158 - a similar tutorial request that will come up via tasks later\n* TODO: Maybe a new issue request for the multiplayer dedicated one for a better write-up\n\n# Tags\n\n(These get entered separately on the GCI site, so they don\'t count toward the body character count limit)\n\n* Tag 1\n* Tag 2\n* Tag 3 ...\n\n# Meta\n\nThis card can be a task series incrementally building a more advanced tutorial chapter by chapter. It could also lead to https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/issues/2158 which might be a separate but closely related wikis specifically on events, interactions, and inventory',NULL,0,'15x Tutorials: ES, events, multiplayer',65536,'https://trello.com/c/yp8Vmlm5','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b12a5484539133a006dc9'),('5b9eff39213e8565a7d90f93',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.884399','2018-10-16 06:44:57.712000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.884400','{emoji={}}','# Title (card name)\n\nAs part of GSOC 2018 the [multi-world project](https://trello.com/c/dYU1iOul/38-theflash98-multi-world) overhauled one of our main UI flows: how to create a new game. We\'d like to get some fresh eyes to review both the old and new approach, comparing and critiquing what\'s better, what\'s worse (if any) and what can still be improved.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* A thread is posted in the [suggestions forum](https://forum.terasology.org/forum/suggestions.21/) with notes from your experimenting, ideas for what could be better, what seemed to you to be missing, and so on\n* Include at least one screenshot highlighting something you want to draw attention to, or even a small video snippet / gif.\n* Optional: Consider showing a UI flow from another game you believe could yield some related inspiration for further UI improvements for this part of Terasology\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Grab an older stable release such as [Alpha 9](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/releases/download/v1.6.0/TerasologyOmega.zip) and experiment with starting and configuring a new game. Try a few games differently. Take notes about what happened and what stuck out to you\n* Grab the [very latest developer build](http://jenkins.terasology.org/job/DistroOmega/lastSuccessfulBuild/artifact/distros/omega/build/distributions/TerasologyOmega.zip) (or a very recent one anyway if somebody broke the newest..) and do the same\n* Compare your notes for the two different game versions and come up with some ideas for improvements\n\n# See also\n\n* Flash\'s [GSOC blog](https://theflash98.github.io/) entries related to his work on reworking the create game flow\n\n# Tags\n\n(These get entered separately on the GCI site, so they don\'t count toward the body character count limit)\n\n* UI\n* UX\n* Comparison\n* Write-up',NULL,0,'Review and critique changes to Create Game workflow',65536,'https://trello.com/c/luW3amKs','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b12d3e21cdd11a9efbf77'),('5b9f483e054aab25d2e8e3e6',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.819512','2019-10-04 03:06:22.051000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.819514','{emoji={}}','# Design utility interface\n\nSince last GCI, we have gained some small utilities to ease new content creation for Destination Sol. There is however only a few of those, and they look very rough. So, your task will be to design interface of new utility such as the existing, or redesign interface of old one, to look more appealing and easier to control to new content creators.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* A sketch of the new UI window(s) is made and published on our [forum](https://forum.terasology.org/forum/) TODO possibly link to specific subforum\n* Once done, supply a link to the post in here\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Take a look at the existing utilities to see how they look like and what they do\n* Pop-in to our chat to ask for help or suggestions if you need so! (https://forum.terasology.org/pages/chat/)\n\n# See also\n\n* Other existing utilities at https://github.com/MovingBlocks/DestSolMisc\n* Optional followup task on implementing the utility in language of your choice at TODO create and link task, or even decide if plausible and not too hard\n\n# Tags\n\n* Design\n* UI/UX',NULL,0,'Design utility interface',1748990,'https://trello.com/c/fn9hOLEL','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b19'),('5b9fb4268ea94e5a5ffc4bf9',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.370928','2018-10-22 15:35:37.338000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.370929','{emoji={}}','# Use and provide feedback for our Blender addon(s)\n\nWe use two small Blender addons to take models from Blender and export them into usable game assets. The main one is used for creatures and has a [nice tutorial](https://github.com/Terasology/TutorialAssetSystem/wiki#blender-addon-for-creatures) that came out of some GSOC 2017 work.\n\nThe goal of this task is to try out the tutorial and take a raw Blender model to working in-game asset.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Functioning game assets have been submitted to a module repo on GitHub\n* One or more screenshots (or a video) of the creature working in-game have been submitted either via link in the GCI task, PR to an existing module, or via forum thread\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Go through the game asset tutorial and especially the [three chapters on the creature addon](https://github.com/Terasology/TutorialAssetSystem/wiki#blender-addon-for-creatures)\n* Look for previously contributed Blender models at https://github.com/MetaTerasology (or make your own / find some with a CC BY 4.0 compatible license)\n* Fetch or create a game module matching the name of the meta module and make sure your exported game assets work with that module enabled in-game\n\n# See also\n\n* The deer is our traditional example. See its [Blender assets](https://github.com/MetaTerasology/WildAnimals/tree/master/deer) and its [game assets](https://github.com/Terasology/WildAnimals/tree/master/assets)\n* There is also an addon for block shapes with a [pending PR](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/TeraMisc/pull/56) - it needs its own tutorial and review',NULL,0,'Use and provide feedback for our Blender addon(s)',475136,'https://trello.com/c/nIu2p6Vw','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb1400605e0cc6f01a9e124'),('5b9fb6e6b582cd8f10b4cc25',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.182600','2018-10-22 15:35:37.271000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.182601','{emoji={}}','# Review tutorials for accuracy and training value\n\nWe have a series of tutorial repos with wikis on GitHub. See [this search](https://github.com/Terasology?q=Tutorial) - they come in different shapes and sizes, some are up to date and accurate while others need fixes or even overhauls to be more worthwhile for training new contributors.\n\nGoal for this task is to go review one of the tutorials for value and accuracy, adding updates if needed, and giving feedback about the current quality of the tutorial.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* An issue and/or PR is submitted to one tutorial repo with feedback and/or changes to improve the tutorial.\n* Feedback should reference several existing bits of wiki text and explain how it could be improved (inaccurate? Poor wording? Confusing?)\n* Include some additional suggestions of what you think should be added to the tutorial\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Use [this search](https://github.com/Terasology?q=Tutorial) to pick a tutorial, consider coordinating with other students in case some might be looking at the same tutorial, or try one that seems more obscure / difficult\n* Try out the tutorial with code if you can (but if you can find enough issues just with the wiki text to provide substantial feedback that\'s OK too)\n\n# See also\n\n* Other tutorials than the one you\'re working on - the world generation and asset tutorials are among the best we have, what makes them good and how could that be applied to the other tutorials?',NULL,0,'Review tutorials for accuracy and training value',81920,'https://trello.com/c/TeuObDmy','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb13feff9698564f44ccc4b'),('5ba12cc1566f1d45a889bc05',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.657760','2018-10-14 03:37:13.796000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.657761',NULL,'',NULL,0,'Create an automation bot to validate bad icon sizes on PR',1519620,'https://trello.com/c/414PbtgP','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b18'),('5ba12d5f52137937707f822b',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.667116','2018-10-14 03:36:34.412000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.667118',NULL,'',NULL,0,'Implement mailing list sign up on Terasology',1585150,'https://trello.com/c/iFKjLiRf','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b18'),('5ba12e0d6000632fb2d0457e',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.675578','2018-10-14 03:37:03.403000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.675579',NULL,'',NULL,0,'Create a dev website for Terasology',1650690,'https://trello.com/c/OmFZnq48','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b18'),('5ba12e460fa07c6580112897',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.684467','2018-10-14 03:36:56.394000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.684468',NULL,'',NULL,0,'Propose and write a useful page to add to Terasology website',1716220,'https://trello.com/c/pioOPRyP','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b18'),('5ba1300c4a64cf69594a2457',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.692392','2018-09-19 03:04:24.386000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.692393',NULL,'',NULL,0,'Update materialize and make sure there are no issues on the update',1781760,'https://trello.com/c/mSUJU8uc','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b18'),('5ba83fda2187887a5ee1a1fd',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.700980','2018-09-24 11:37:50.127000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.700981','{emoji={}}','See https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/pull/3475 for a related PR',NULL,0,'Write tutorial for working various profilers for the game and how to spot typical performance issues',1847300,'https://trello.com/c/xRLcInnq','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b18'),('5ba8505230e1aa839ec6f45f',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.708942','2018-09-28 01:01:06.733000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.708943','{emoji={}}','Terasology uses a file with the extension shape that describes a given block. Shape files for Terasology are implemented through a blender plugin. Since the data is saved to a text based json format; it\'s possible to make the block using a text editor but the plugin makes this process a lot easier. the goal of this task is to create a simple shape that can be used for a custom block. \n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* \n\n# Where to start\n \n* https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/Shape-Architecture\n* plugin: https://github.com/MovingBlocks/TeraMisc/tree/master/blender_addons\n\n# See also\n\n\n* example shape: https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/blob/develop/modules/Core/assets/shapes/door.shape\n* blender shapes: https://github.com/MovingBlocks/TeraMisc/tree/master/block_shapes\n\n# Tags\n\n* 3d\n* blender\n* mods',NULL,0,'Install Block Plugin And Create Block Mesh',1912830,'https://trello.com/c/ep5jW5d0','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b18'),('5ba850a0ab6be74649a5d084',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.802161','2018-10-08 04:43:33.395000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.802163','{emoji={}}','It\'s nice to have a shape, but  it would actually be useful if the shape was actually in the game. the goal of this task is the implement the shape that you designed and add it to the game as a block. \n\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* \n\n# Where to start\n \n* https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/Shape-Architecture\n* plugin: https://github.com/MovingBlocks/TeraMisc/tree/master/blender_addons\n\n# See also\n\n# Tags\n\n* 3d\n* blender\n* mods',NULL,0,'Use Shape in a custom block',384000,'https://trello.com/c/KwK49se9','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b19'),('5ba87b27aa83a6726c08b599',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.794627','2018-10-21 04:46:00.336000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.794628','{emoji={}}','After you\'ve made your custom block it will need to have some textures. the blender plugin only exports the texture coordinates so the texture itself will have to be added to terasology add assigned to the associated block.\n\n\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9Ha2rFR6qO0',NULL,0,'Texture Custom Block',288000,'https://trello.com/c/MOSoNStI','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b19'),('5babd1b7e5da384e7428ed83',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.457491','2019-10-16 22:38:58.765000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.457492','{emoji={}}','# Replay Test: Walking Long Distance\n\nWith the new Record and Replay (R&R) feature we can now record a game using the Core module and then use that recording to test the game.\n\nThis task is to use R&R as well as `TestReplayModule` to record a game using the Core module, in which the player walks a long distance, and the test checks they reach the correct position\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* A Replay Test that executes a replay in which the player walks for at least a minute and then asserts the player\'s initial and final location.\n* A video showing the replay running on the headed test environment and the assert passing.\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Get `TestReplayModule` on your workspace. [Instructions on how to fetch a module](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/Developing-Modules)\n* [Read about Replay Tests on the wiki](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/Replay-Tests)\n* [Check the example test code](https://github.com/Terasology/TestReplayModule/blob/master/src/test/java/org/terasology/replayTests/examples/ExampleAcceptanceTest.java) to understand how to get the `LocalPlayer` from the game.\n* Get the necessary data for the test from the `LocalPlayer` or `CoreRegistry`\n\n# See also\n\n* [The Record and Replay Wiki](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/How-to-Use-Record-and-Replay)\n',NULL,0,'Replay Test: Walking Long Distance',1978370,'https://trello.com/c/n3UDraWL','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5da6ffb280d00419145f796a'),('5baffcc32d7a35664b173a11',NULL,0,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.955294','2018-10-23 16:09:52.962000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.955296','{emoji={}}','Students that as existing contributors are helping with initial setup of GCI, but should be removed from Trello + the Slack channel before the contest starts (and naturally not be invited to the GCI site itself at all)',NULL,0,'Students to evict from Trello/Slack',180224,'https://trello.com/c/Tahx8oKW','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b16'),('5bb0ed56551dc30f05a7b7cd',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.965136','2018-10-01 01:36:03.086000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.965137','{emoji={}}','https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/GCI#master-of-oreon\n\nWe should add links to some MOO tasks when GCI goes lives',NULL,0,'Focus area: Master of Oreon',245760,'https://trello.com/c/YcRMFh9O','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b16'),('5bb0f08ecc6b265873ef9bef',NULL,0,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.495034','2018-10-25 01:23:11.485000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.495034','{emoji={}}','# Title (card name)\n\nIntro text - describe the involved stuff (code, component, website, document, etc) briefly, what\'s missing, and what\'s desired\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Put bullet points here for the final state that\'ll satisfy the task\n* Include at least one \"deliverable\" - usually a screenshot for any task involving game assets (forces testing of the game - if it doesn\'t work yet then the task isn\'t done yet, ask for help!), a forum thread or wiki page for a document, a youtube 