urrently being used.\n[Post](https://forum.terasology.org/threads/master-of-oreon.1015/post-16075) to get students started and [wiki](http://github.com/Terasology/MasterOfOreon/wiki)',NULL,0,'Master Of Oreon',2109440,'https://trello.com/c/gAGVZLdf','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b18'),('5bb10bb43f2d4415371e5c25',NULL,0,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.502923','2018-10-27 01:07:24.458000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.502923','{emoji={}}','# Title (card name)\n\nIntro text - describe the involved stuff (code, component, website, document, etc) briefly, what\'s missing, and what\'s desired\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Put bullet points here for the final state that\'ll satisfy the task\n* Include at least one \"deliverable\" - usually a screenshot for any task involving game assets (forces testing of the game - if it doesn\'t work yet then the task isn\'t done yet, ask for help!), a forum thread or wiki page for a document, a youtube link for a video, and so on\n\n# Where to start\n\n* More bullet points! Give the student instructions for the starting state to aim for (working workspace etc)\n* Give names of classes or other code resources to search for, if applicable\n* Link to related information to investigate\n\n# See also\n\n* Put a link here to a section on https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/GCI if there is one describing this specific category of task\n* Any other information that may be relevant, such as suggested tasks to',NULL,0,'Naman - 1 task every 2 days',49152,'https://trello.com/c/dKCCUkzW','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b1d'),('5bb1162c641aec0e53f86656',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.155278','2018-10-24 03:31:24.444000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.155279','{emoji={}}','# New crop blocks for planting\n\nThe Master of Oreon module currently only has one type of crop, the Cookie Crops, which can be planted by the Oreons. These crops also have different stages of growth defined which are handled in-game by the Changing Blocks module.\nThis task requires you to create a new block for a \"unique\" crop type of your choice with atleast 5 different stages of growth.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Use the block in-game and provide screenshots(or preferably a video) showcasing the different stages of growth of your crop.\n* The crop should have atleast 5 stages of growth.\n* Open a PR in the Master Of Oreon repository.\n\n# Where to start\n\n* [Forum thread](https://forum.terasology.org/threads/master-of-oreon.1015/post-16075)\n* See this [asset folder](https://github.com/Terasology/MasterOfOreon/tree/master/assets/blocks/OreonCrop) in the Master of Oreon repository for an example.\n* See this [blog post](https://naman-sopho.github.io/2018-06-19-GSoCWeek6/) for a brief description about the current state of crops in MOO.\n\n# See also\n\n* [Changing Blocks readme](https://github.com/Terasology/ChangingBlocks#changingblocks)\n* _Link to task for adding this crop to the MOO game flow_\n\n# Tags\n\n(These get entered separately on the GCI site, so they don\'t count toward the body character count limit)\n\n* Design\n* Master of Oreon',NULL,0,'MOO Crops (I) - New Crop blocks for planting',2273280,'https://trello.com/c/tXm5a2tl','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb13fe396623c2292321640'),('5bb18cf53b34fb372906c8b9',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.756155','2018-10-01 12:56:53.480000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.756156',NULL,'',NULL,0,'add a tutorial book to an existing module: x, x, x, x',2174980,'https://trello.com/c/P191kAcR','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b18'),('5bb18d1a9a052c0f5643fb66',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.619529','2018-10-20 21:14:34.826000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.619530','{emoji={}}','K Computers is the newest module added Terasology over GSOC. the goal of this task is to implement a small lua script demonstrating the functionality of the moudule.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Demonstrate the functionality of the code \n\n# Where to start\n\n* kcomputer module: https://github.com/Terasology/KComputers\n* run ```groovw recurse kcomputer``` to download the module to your workspace\n\n# Tags\n\n* Rails\n* Module\n\n',NULL,0,'write a sample lua script for KComputers',98303,'https://trello.com/c/Y169WEOO','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b18'),('5bb1ad37351a9c4e5ca0ae0c',NULL,0,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.784514','2018-10-15 16:06:15.436000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.784515','{emoji={}}','slerp is similar to lerp but this involves rotation instead of position. For a quaternion this would focus on the interpolation  of one quaternion to the rotation of another quaternion. some sample code is available on Wikipedia to look at for the implementation: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Slerp\n\n',NULL,0,'Termath: implement slerp for vector',4096,'https://trello.com/c/gSvalk5O','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b1a'),('5bb1ad94a39b230f9236ee68',NULL,0,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.774603','2018-10-15 16:06:13.238000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.774604',NULL,'',NULL,0,'TeraMath: angle between two vectors',2048,'https://trello.com/c/aOD7bdM7','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b1a'),('5bb2de6cedc1097d3d77a5c7',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.765242','2018-10-02 12:59:23.286000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.765243','{emoji={}}','Example (and probably one we should enable ourselves sometime): https://probot.github.io/apps/first-timers/\n\nWe could likely make this into a task series with one bot doing one simple thing, which is how Probot is generally used. It could perhaps take over some of the GooeyHub stuff too, but some of these tasks take Jenkins access etc making them not suitable for GCI\n\nIt is possible we can find some simpler cases like stellargo\'s answer to https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/issues/3345 and turn those into GCI tasks, with each app being a \"type\" of Gooey with one of the graphics. So if somebody submits code with violations angry red gooey could show up and gently but also firmly instruct about that issue ;-)',NULL,0,'Probot stuffs',2437120,'https://trello.com/c/vnq4Hrlq','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b18'),('5bb396b91b70dc419eda850f',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.362270','2019-10-16 23:42:11.242000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.362270','{emoji={}}','# Improve wiki page for DS json details\n\nDestination Sol uses some JSON files to configure how the different solar systems work, what kinds of equipment ships start with, what loot drops, and so on. The current wiki documentation doesn\'t quite cover everything, so this task is meant to go over it and cover any missing details. \n\nFor instance in `systeConfig.json` there are lines like the following: `\"items\": \"core:fixedGun 0.5|core:lightArmor 0.75|core:smallShield+core:shield\"` - what is the meaning of the `|` and `+` ? Find out and document it somewhere! Same for anything else you can find that isn\'t currently covered in the wiki\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* You\'ve identified and fixed several omissions in the DestSol wiki and edited them into existing or new pages (such as what the `+` means)\n* Supply a link to a page you\'ve changed and explain what\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Study the existing wiki, such as the [JSON Tutorial](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/DestinationSol/wiki/JSON-tutorial) and the [Creating a Ship](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/DestinationSol/wiki/Creating-a-Ship) page \n* Look at some of the JSON files like `systemConfig` - look for interesting stuff that doesn\'t seem obvious. Is it described anywhere in the wiki?\n* Edit the file and see if you can figure out what happens! Then document it\n\n# See also\n\n* [The developer setup for DestSol](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/DestinationSol/wiki/Full-Workspace-Setup) to get a working source workspace\n* TODO: Other similar DS tasks',NULL,0,'Improve wiki page for DS json details',409600,'https://trello.com/c/k3sAqtbe','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb1400605e0cc6f01a9e124'),('5bb3b9488d0dad39b9c19a25',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.049682','2018-10-24 03:31:38.511000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.049682','{emoji={}}','# Add a new crop block to Master Of Oreon\n\nThis is a follow up task to <link for the \"New crop block task\"> which requires you to add the new block created to the Master of Oreon module such that a `plant` task can be created for this crop and it can be planted by the Oreons in the game.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Implement a task for planting the new crop and also define the attributes of this new resource.\n* Open a PR in the MOO repository with the required changes.\n* Share a screenshot(or preferably a video) with a field of the newly added crops in the game.\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Go through the `PerformTaskNode` for the logic related to task completion.\n\n# See also\n\n* This[ wiki](https://github.com/Terasology/MasterOfOreon/wiki/Resources) for details on how to add the crop block as a resource.\n\n# Tags\n\n(These get entered separately on the GCI site, so they don\'t count toward the body character count limit)\n\n* Master Of Oreon',NULL,0,'MOO Crops (II) - Add the new crop block to the game',2437120,'https://trello.com/c/gRx0VRgb','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb10eaaa163492c93420393'),('5bb55af78dc29689e6a5c2b1',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.099605','2018-10-23 03:59:27.501000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.099606','{emoji={}}','# Add option to trust all URLs to the same website\n\nParts of the GUI in Terasology can link to websites, and Terasology will open a browser to that address. However, not all links can be trusted so the user has to confirm if they want to navigate to it. The user can also opt to always trust the URL to avoid having to confirm each time they open it.\n\n[This is what the system looks like at the moment](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/26657147/46326907-5fc12700-c5d5-11e8-96d0-87073b414f66.png).\n\nThis task is to add the option to trust all URLs to that website. For instance, in the screenshot there should be an option to trust all links to `https://githu