.065989','{emoji={}}','\nAdvanced Task see other MOO related tasks first.\nOreons currently have `Strength` and `Intelligence` attributes assigned randomly to them when they are spawned and they also posses other attributes like `Hunger` which are incremented when they perform a task. These should affect when tasks are assigned to the Oreons, for instance a hungry Oreon should not be given a task if another Oreon is available or an Intelligent Oreon should be preferred for a Research task.\nYour task is to implement the logic for a system which takes into account the attributes of an oreon before assigning tasks to it.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Open a PR in the Master of Oreon repository with the required changes.\n\n# Where to start\n\n* See the `TaskManagementSystem` and `LookForTaskNode` for the task search and assignment logic\n\n# Tags\n\n(These get entered separately on the GCI site, so they don\'t count toward the body character count limit)\n\n* Master Of Oreon\n* Tasks',NULL,0,'Oreon attributes affect task assignment',2568190,'https://trello.com/c/9r7hTXcQ','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb10eaaa163492c93420393'),('5bbcd0b12235b94ecbd1fbae',NULL,0,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.695077','2018-11-10 02:54:52.184000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.695077',NULL,'# Title (card name)\n\nIntro text - describe the involved stuff (code, component, website, document, etc) briefly, what\'s missing, and what\'s desired\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Put bullet points here for the final state that\'ll satisfy the task\n* Include at least one \"deliverable\" - usually a screenshot for any task involving game assets (forces testing of the game - if it doesn\'t work yet then the task isn\'t done yet, ask for help!), a forum thread or wiki page for a document, a youtube link for a video, and so on\n\n# Where to start\n\n* More bullet points! Give the student instructions for the starting state to aim for (working workspace etc)\n* Give names of classes or other code resources to search 