ssue relevant to this task](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/GooeyJr/issues/44)',NULL,0,'GooeyJr: Enhance issues.coffee',1683460,'https://trello.com/c/a9evh0wc','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5da70003a4f3d68a8d822ff2'),('5bc18d9c9bbb355f094a119d',NULL,0,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.328766','2018-10-13 17:53:58.811000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.328767',NULL,'',NULL,0,'GooeyJr: Allow issues.coffee to work with URLs',65535,'https://trello.com/c/zjk2E4Gj','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb1400605e0cc6f01a9e124'),('5bc21690dbc62b37386af113',NULL,0,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.671254','2018-11-10 02:54:58.750000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.671255',NULL,'# Title (card name)\n\nIntro text - describe the involved stuff (code, component, website, document, etc) briefly, what\'s missing, and what\'s desired\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Put bullet points here for the final state that\'ll satisfy the task\n* Include at least one \"deliverable\" - usually a screenshot for any task involving game assets (forces testing of the game - if it doesn\'t work yet then the task isn\'t done yet, ask for help!), a forum thread or wiki page for a document, a youtube link for a video, and so on\n\n# Where to start\n\n* More bullet points! Give the student instructions for the starting state to aim for (working workspace etc)\n* Give names of classes or other code resources to search for, if applicable\n* Link to related information to investigate\n\n# See also\n\n* Put a link here to a section on https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/GCI if there is one describing this specific category of task\n* Any other information that may be relevant, such as suggested tasks to consider before or after this task\n\n# Tags\n\n(These get entered separately on the GCI site, so they don\'t count toward the body character count limit)\n\n* Tag 1\n* Tag 2\n* Tag 3 ...',NULL,0,'Cerv - 1 task every 2 days',512,'https://trello.com/c/GwIcpKig','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb0f06bf9698564f444f403'),('5bc24e9060e3e5314ceb6d40',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.413099','2019-10-16 23:07:12.365000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.413099','{emoji={}}','Because of how modular and super-hackable Terasology is, we have had a lot of interesting gameplay modules pop up over the years. One of our newest gameplay modules is [GooKeeper](https://github.com/Terasology/GooKeeper), a SlimeRancher-esque gamemode where players have to capture gooeys and build a zoo to make a living.\n\nA key aspect of GooKeeper is the economy system: players get money (ingame, of course) from visitors visiting the zoo. A natural question to ask is \"What can the players do with money?\". Currently, the answer would be \"nothing\". That\'s where you come in. Your task, should you choose to accept it, is to design a new item/structure that players will be able to purchase in GooKeeper.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* An issue has been submitted to the GooKeeper [repository](https://github.com/Terasology/GooKeeper) describing your new item. Your writeup should include the name of the item, what it would do, and why players would want to buy it (how will it be useful for them).\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Join our IRC or Discord to chat about potential ideas.\n* Here\'s an example idea: vending machines where visitors can buy stuff (more money!)',NULL,0,'GooKeeper: Design New Purchasable',1880060,'https://trello.com/c/zRU8C3iP','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5da70003a4f3d68a8d822ff2'),('5bc3682fc824ea3ebde1e335',NULL,0,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.662062','2018-11-10 02:55:02.275000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.662063',NULL,'# Title (card name)\n\nIntro text - describe the involved stuff (code, component, website, document, etc) briefly, what\'s missing, and what\'s desired\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Put bullet points here for the final state that\'ll satisfy the task\n* Include at least one \"deliverable\" - usually a screenshot for any task involving game assets (forces testing of the game - if it doesn\'t work yet then the task isn\'t done yet, ask for help!),