3e35eaabb9743f196fb1',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.438725','2019-10-16 22:36:26.930000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.438726','{emoji={}}','# Replay Test: Railgun\n\nWith the new Record and Replay (R&R) feature we can now record a game using the Core module and then use that recording to test the game.\n\nOne of the items in Core is a railgun which can explode things from a distance. Use R&R as well as `TestReplayModule` to make a test to check that the railgun explodes things properly\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* A Replay Test that executes a replay in which the player explodes something from a distance using the railgun and then asserts the destruction of some of the exploded blocks.\n* A video showing the replay running on the headed test environment and the assert passing.\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Get `TestReplayModule` on your workspace. [Instructions on how to fetch a module](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/Developing-Modules)\n* [Read about Replay Tests on the wiki](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/Replay-Tests)\n* [Check the example test code](https://github.com/Terasology/TestReplayModule/blob/master/src/test/java/org/terasology/replayTests/examples/ExampleAcceptanceTest.java) to understand how to get the `LocalPlayer` from the game.\n* Get the necessary data for the test from the `LocalPlayer` or `CoreRegistry`\n\n# See also\n\n* [The Record and Replay Wiki](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/How-to-Use-Record-and-Replay)\n* [The task to write a replay test for character death](https://codein.withgoogle.com/dashboard/tasks/5670478598373376/)\n* [The task to write a replay test for walking long distances](https://codein.withgoogle.com/dashboard/tasks/4694374333022208/)',NULL,0,'Replay Test: Railgun',1847300,'https://trello.com/c/5aCAMhFD','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5da6ffb280d00419145f796a'),('5bc43e5a66506515ee327af1',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.466680','2019-10-16 22:39:25.690000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.466681','{emoji={}}','# Replay Test: Explode Tool\n\nWith the new Record and Replay (R&R) feature we can now record a game using the Core module and then use that recording to test the game.\n\nOne of the items in Core is the *Explode Tool* which the player can use to explode things. Your task is to use R&R as well as `TestReplayModule ` to make a test that checks the tool explodes stuff properly\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* A Replay Test that executes a replay in which the player explodes something using the explode tool and then asserts the destruction of some of the exploded blocks.\n* A video showing the replay running on the headed test environment and the assert passing.\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Get `TestReplayModule` on your workspace. [Instructions on how to fetch a module](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/Developing-Modules)\n* [Read about Replay Tests on the wiki](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/Replay-Tests)\n* [Check the example test code](https://github.com/Terasology/TestReplayModule/blob/master/src/test/java/org/terasology/replayTests/examples/ExampleAcceptanceTest.java) to understand how to get the `LocalPlayer` from the game.\n* Get the necessary data for the test from the `LocalPlayer` or `CoreRegistry`\n\n# See also\n\n* [The Record and Replay Wiki](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/How-to-Use-Record-and-Replay)\n',NULL,0,'Replay Test: Explode Tool',2043900,'https://trello.com/c/ZkDkflGw','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5da6ffb280d00419145f796a'),('5bc43ebe35a6d1418fec762d',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.248864','2018-10-23 00:43:55.661000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.248865','{emoji={}}','# Replay Test: Player Character Death\n\nWith the new Record and Replay (R&R) feature we can now record a game using the Core module and then use that recording to test the game.\n\nBeing able to die is an important part of Terasology, so this task is to make a test for it.  \nUsing R&R as well as `TestReplayModule ` make a test where the player falls from a great height and dies.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* A Replay Test that executes a replay in which the player character dies and then asserts the character death.\n* A video showing the replay running on the headed test environment and the assert passing.\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Get `TestReplayModule` on your workspace. [Instructions on how to fetch a module](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/Developing-Modules)\n* [Read about Replay Tests on the wiki](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/Replay-Tests)\n* [Check the example test code](https://github.com/Terasology/TestReplayModule/blob/master/src/test/java/org/terasology/replayTests/examples/ExampleAcceptanceTest.java) to understand how to get the `LocalPlayer` from the game.\n* Get the necessary data for the test from the `LocalPlayer` or `CoreRegistry`\n\n# See also\n\n* [The Record and Replay Wiki](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/How-to-Use-Record-and-Replay)\n* [The task to write a test for walking long distances](https://codein.withgoogle.com/dashboard/tasks/4694374333022208/)\n* [The task to write a test for healing HP](https://codein.withgoogle.com/dashboard/tasks/6062344837791744/)',NULL,0,'Replay Test: Player Character Death',294912,'https://trello.com/c/DyIs0Ff3','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb13ffda245836ef12b392c'),('5bc43ed68d6a3a85b52f0f3e',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.258517','2018-10-23 04:11:39.092000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.258521','{emoji={}}','# Replay Test: Recover HP\n\nWith the new Record and Replay (R&R) feature we can now record a game using the Core module and then use that recording to test the game.\n\nTerasology has a number of ways to heal yourself. It would not be very good if they didn\'t work. This task is to use R&R along with `TestReplayModule` to add in a test where the player takes some damage, and then heals it back.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* A Replay Test that executes a replay in which the player character at some point doesn\'t have full HP but then after some time does.\n* A video showing the replay running on the headed test environment and the assert passing.\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Get `TestReplayModule` on your workspace. [Instructions on how to fetch a module](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/Developing-Modules)\n* [Read about Replay Tests on the wiki](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/Replay-Tests)\n* [Check the example test code](https://github.com/Terasology/TestReplayModule/blob/master/src/test/java/org/terasology/replayTests/examples/ExampleAcceptanceTest.java) to understand how to get the `LocalPlayer` from the game.\n* Get the necessary data for the test from the `LocalPlayer` or `CoreRegistry`\n\n# See also\n\n* [The Record and Replay Wiki](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/How-to-Use-Record-and-Replay)\n',NULL,0,'Replay Test: Recover HP',360448,'https://trello.com/c/hNKnDpHd','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb13ffda245836ef12b392c'),('5bc4de18e1fafb84f5c9a24f',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.190703','2018-10-22 15:35:37.270000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.190703','{emoji={}}','# Write a tutorial for Genome implementations\nTerasology\'s [Genome](https://github.com/Terasology/Genome) module is a versatile general-purpose utility module which can be used to implement genetic features in other modules.\n\nFor example, an \"Animals\" module could use Genome to simulate how biological characteristics such as height and color change from generation to generation due to genetic factors. This involves making those characteristics depend on a gene in the animal\'s genome, and then using a breeding algorithm during mating which would determine how genes from two parents are mixed to form the genes of the offspring.\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* A wiki article is created containing a tutorial on how someone could implement Genome in their module.\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Go through the Genome module to get a sense of how it is set up. The Javadocs should be useful.\n* Try to figure out how the setup could be used in another module.\n* Speak to mentors on IRC if you have questions on how Genome works.\n\n# See also\n\n* The [Genome module](https://github.com/Terasology/Genome)\n* The [WildAnimalsGenome module](https://github.com/Terasology/WildAnimalsGenome) which uses Genome to make a deer\'s speed dependent on its genes',NULL,0,'Write a tutorial for Genome implementations',147456,'https://trello.com/c/UxVwy4Y0','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb13feff9698564f44ccc4b'),('5bc4f5a8d78ab3606ab1c894',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.006531','2018-10-22 15:35:12.462000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.006532','{emoji={}}','Advanced task! The earlier world gen tasks should still be available, and we suggest completing most/all of them first :)\n\nWhile Terasology at present does not support multiple worlds completely yet, we can pretty much cheat and just create a world layer deep under (or above) ground that looks vastly different, then provide a way for the player to travel there and back (the distance should be unfeasible to travel manually)\n\nThe goal of this task will be to implement a \"dimension\" like the Minecraft Nether, far below ground with stuff like magma seas, different basic world blocks, different flora, and maybe one or two other terrain features.\n\nKey to this will be defining an alternative surface deep below (or above) ground. Look at the existing classes related to surfaces and sea level. You do not want to have the player start in the alternative \"dimension\" so the underworld should not be any kind of default.\n\nThere should be some way for the player to travel to the other world. Could provide a block with an activation event (it can be e clicked).\n\nAn underworld should probably have a ceiling low enough to not start regenerating sunlight. Provide alternative light sources (lava or other lighted blocks)\n\n# Definition of Done\n\n* Submit a repository that contains the module for the Additional Dimension.\n* Add a README to the repository that you submit, describing what your alternate dimension is and what unique features it has.\n* Add a few screenshots from the alternate dimension to the README in the repository. Also add a screenshot of the travel block, if you have one.\n* Describe the mechanism to transport the player to the alternate dimension in the README.\n\n# Resources:\n\n* Inferno is a great example of an alternate dimension- https://github.com/Terasology/Inferno',NULL,0,'Advanced World Gen- Create an \"alternative dimension\" layer and a way to get the player there',2011140,'https://trello.com/c/iMit2oKd','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb10eaaa163492c93420393'),('5bc4f9be944295152dd06d2e',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.430704','2019-10-16 22:32:56.348000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.430704','{emoji={}}','The [SimpleFarming](https://github.com/Terasology/SimpleFarming) module adds support for various kinds of plants and their growth. Currently, SimpleFarming supports plants which grow from a seed to a sapling to a plant, and vines which are multi-block plants which start from seeds and grow horizontally along the ground.\n\nThis task aims at adding support for trees which grow vertically (think of this as a \"vertical vine\"). At the end of this task, you should be able to plant a kind of seed which will slowly grow into a tall tree, full with a wooden trunk and leaves.\n\n**This task is harder than other tasks. We will do our best to assist but you should have completed other tasks first**\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* A PR is submitted to the SimpleFarming module which implements tree growth. You must also add a seed (and other required blocks) that can be planted to get full trees.\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Check out how vines currently grow. You should, in principle, be able to apply the same concept (with modifications) to make a tree that grows vertically.\n\n# See also\n\n* The [SimpleFarming](https://github.com/Terasology/SimpleFarming) module',NULL,0,'SimpleFarming: Add support for growing trees',1781760,'https://trello.com/c/v3nTcIkf','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5da6ffb280d00419145f796a'),('5bc50c15ec2eb06c0543b3ba',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.199342','2019-10-16 22:22:43.727000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.199343','{emoji={}}','#Write a tutorial for Structure Templates\nTerasology\'s [Structure Template](https://github.com/Terasology/StructureTemplates) module implements structure templates that can be used to spawn the same building over and over again, either using an item or programmatically.\n\nAll the documentation for using it currently resides in the repository [readme](https://github.com/Terasology/StructureTemplates/blob/master/README.md). There\'s a bunch of information in a few forum threads that are scattered around. \n\nThis task is centered around creating a formal tutorial like the [World Generation Tutorial](https://github.com/Terasology/TutorialWorldGeneration).\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\nA repository with an example of structure templates that also demostrates their use in-game. Along the lines of [World Generation Tutorial](https://github.com/Terasology/TutorialWorldGeneration), the wiki should have a step by step tutorial that instructs the reader on how to-\n\n* Use the structure templates toolbox and other magic tools.\n* Use exisiting structure templates\n* Create new structure templates\n* Use the structure templates programatically as in [GooeysQuests](https://github.com/Terasology/GooeysQuests).\n\n# Where to start\n\n* A guide to creating modules can be found [here](https://github.com/Terasology/StructureTemplates/blob/master/README.md). [GooeysQuests](https://github.com/Terasology/GooeysQuests) is an example of a module that uses structure templates to spawn dungeons (the templates\' code is located at assets/prefabs/structures in the module\'s repo)\n* The forum threads for [GooeysQuests](https://github.com/Terasology/GooeysQuests) and [StructuralTemplates](http://forum.terasology.org/threads/structure-templates.1550/) help introduce the system further',NULL,0,'Write a tutorial for Structure Templates',212992,'https://trello.com/c/cpjStE1D','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb13feff9698564f44ccc4b'),('5bc60b14e490cf40a1a784f4',NULL,0,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.643575','2018-10-23 17:20:21.377000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.643575',NULL,'# Title (card name)\n\nIntro text - describe the involved stuff (code, component, website, document, etc) briefly, what\'s missing, and what\'s desired\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Put bullet points here for the final state that\'ll satisfy the task\n* Include at least one \"deliverable\" - usually a screenshot for any task involving game assets (forces testing of the game - if it doesn\'t work yet then the task isn\'t done yet, ask for help!), a forum thread or wiki page for a document, a youtube link for a video, and so on\n\n# Where to start\n\n* More bullet points! Give the student instructions for the starting state to aim for (working workspace etc)\n* Give names of classes or other code resources to search for, if applicable\n* Link to related information to investigate\n\n# See also\n\n* Put a link here to a section on https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/GCI if there is one describing this specific category of task\n* Any other information that may be relevant, such as suggested tasks to consider before or after this task\n\n# Tags\n\n(These get entered separately on the GCI site, so they don\'t count toward the body character count limit)\n\n* Tag 1\n* Tag 2\n* Tag 3 ...',NULL,0,'Cerv - 1 task every 2 days',128,'https://trello.com/c/QqgL2mzC','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb0f06bf9698564f444f403'),('5bc62e5e7d589082d8505d5a',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.737479','2018-10-18 03:32:20.157000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.737480',NULL,'# Title (card name)\n\nIntro text - describe the involved stuff (code, component, website, document, etc) briefly, what\'s missing, and what\'s desired\n\n# Definition of \'D