pace) or even [run the game from source](https://codein.withgoogle.com/dashboard/tasks/4787385392955392/) before starting!\n\n# Definition of Done\n\n* A PR made to the [main engine repo](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/) that fixes a group of LGTM errors.\n  * Also make sure this doesn\'t introduce any new errors!\n\n# Where to Start\n\n* [Check out the issue for this task for details on how to fix some error groups](\nhttps://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/issues/3510)\n* Have a look [at the errors on the LGTM site](https://lgtm.com/projects/g/MovingBlocks/Terasology/alerts/?mode=tree&severity=error)\n\n# See Also\n* [Report a new bug](https://codein.withgoogle.com/dashboard/tasks/5605165970227200/)\n* [How to get started with Terasology](https://codein.withgoogle.com/dashboard/tasks/6648523383635968/)',NULL,0,'Fix a group of LGTM errors',425984,'https://trello.com/c/VXkjF8OT','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb13ffda245836ef12b392c'),('5bcc783cd27955518b6580f2',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.403020','2019-10-16 23:03:20.104000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.403021','{emoji={}}','#Fix a group of LGTM Warnings\nLGTM is a site which can analyse our code to find errors and parts of the code we can improve. We recently [added it to our project](https://lgtm.com/projects/g/MovingBlocks/Terasology) and we got a bunch of warnings. Your task is to go through and fix a group of warnings. Please only fix one type of warning so that other students can also do this task.\n\n[Prepare your workspace](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/Preparing-an-Engine-Workspace) or even [run the game from source](https://codein.withgoogle.com/dashboard/tasks/4787385392955392/) before starting!\n\n\n# Definition of Done\n\n* A PR made to the [main engine repo](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/) that fixes a group of LGTM warnings.\n  * Also make sure this doesn\'t introduce any new warnings or errors!\n\n# Where to Start\n\n* [Check out the issue for this task for details on how to fix some error groups](\nhttps://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/issues/3510)\n* Have a look [at the warnings on the LGTM site](https://lgtm.com/projects/g/MovingBlocks/Terasology/alerts/?mode=tree&severity=warning)\n\n# See Also\n* Other fix reported issues tasks',NULL,0,'Fix a group of LGTM warnings',1814530,'https://trello.com/c/WY0YcgdO','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5da70003a4f3d68a8d822ff2'),('5bcc842735cffb2064e76c87',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:04.980953','2018-10-24 01:37:42.032000','2020-09-13 00:02:04.980954','{emoji={}}','#Recap your GCI experience with Terasology\n\n_Please submit this task as late as possible, as we are interested in your experience with previous tasks! Ideally this should be the last Google Code-In task you submit, unless you want to pick a big one right before the task claiming period ends (to work on the last three days)_\n\nAs this year\'s Google Code-In is coming to an end, the Terasology project would like to hear any feedback you have on the competition. What were your most - and least - favourite parts of the project? What was your experience with different parts of the codebase? How would you improve the experience for next year\'s students?\n\nPlease note that this can\'t be your first task - complete at least one other task (running the game from source, adding any new content or submitting code...) before starting work on this one!\n\n## Definition of \'Done\'\nA response to the [Google Code-In 2018 Recap Thread]() is created, with the survey template from the starting post filled out. (Copy-paste it to your reply, then answer the 13 questions.)',NULL,0,'Recap your GCI experience with Terasology',540672,'https://trello.com/c/qDHU8Bpj','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b16'),('5bcc851c7969e47a63a0871e',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.207966','2018-10-22 15:35:37.280000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.207967','{emoji={}}','# Fix up module readme\n\nThe readme provides an introduction to a module. Some of the module readme\'s haven\'t been updated in a while. A good readme should provide a strong introduction to someone working or using the module.\n\nA readme is the first thing people see when looking at the module on Github. As such it should provide a quick overview of what the module is. It should list some of the features of the module and point to where more information can be found (If there is any). It\'s a file named readme.md in the top folder of the repository (next to the module.txt file)\n\nStart off by having a look at the readme\'s in [the Terasology repos](http://github.com/Terasology) as well a [the Destination Sol modules](https://github.com/DestinationSol)\n\n# Definition of Done\n* A pull request to the an existing module with a readme that could work with a tweak or an update. This should be at least a few sentences or better yet several sections, but naturally some modules have more to talk about than others\n  * Try and include at least one image in the readme.\n\n# Where to start\n* If possibly try to play the game with the content from the specific module to understand it better\n* [Look at some example readme in Terasology Repos](http://github.com/Terasology)\n  * [The potions module provides devs with info and lists the potions](https://github.com/Terasology/Potions)\n  * [The cooking module gives information on contributing](https://github.com/Terasology/Cooking)',NULL,0,'Fix up module readme',245760,'https://trello.com/c/qikxK2Po','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb13feff9698564f44ccc4b'),('5bcc86bce4356258082ae1e1',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.287172','2018-10-22 15:35:16.289000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.287173','{emoji={}}','# Report a new bug/crash\nAs much as we try Terasology does have some bugs in it, all software does. If you find a bug in Terasology or a module then this is the task for you! Post it onto the relevant issue tracker or update an existing issue.\n\nUse the search to see if it\'s already been reported. If it has then add some extra detail or open a new issue if it hasn\'t been found yet.\n\n**Note:** _Your bug/crash must be a new one, or add something substantial to an existing one. Please use the search option to try and find an existing issue and/or ask a mentor before submitting this task_\n\n# Definition of Done\n* A new comment onto an Issue on a module that provides some useful information about the bug.\n* A new Issue detailing the bug or crash that happened and providing useful info. Screenshots and logs are good things to include.\n\n# Where to Start\n\n* [The github Issue Tracker for the engine](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/issues)\n* Try doing some other tasks to see if you come across any bugs whilst completing them.\n\n# See also\n* Other QA tasks',NULL,0,'Report a new bug/crash',1581060,'https://trello.com/c/njrPPIkp','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5bb13ffda245836ef12b392c'),('5bcca29d058f7847ba7306e4',NULL,0,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.576160','2018-10-23 16:36:59.030000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.576161',NULL,'# Title (card name)\n\nIntro text - describe the involved stuff (code, component, website, document, etc) briefly, what\'s missing, and what\'s desired\n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Put bullet points here for the final state that\'ll satisfy the task\n* Include at least one \"deliverable\" - usually a screenshot for any task involving game assets (forces testing of the game - if it doesn\'t work yet then the task isn\'t done yet, ask for help!), a forum thread or wiki page for a document, a youtube link for a video, and so on\n\n# Where to start\n\n* More bullet points! Give the student instructions for the starting state to aim for (working workspace etc)\n* Give names of classes or other code resources to search for, if applicable\n* Link to related information to investigate\n\n# See also\n\n* Put a link here to a section on https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/GCI if there is one describing this specific category of task\n* Any other information that may be r