sing.\n\n# Where to start\n\n* Get `TestReplayModule` on your workspace. [Instructions on how to fetch a module](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/Developing-Modules).\n* [Read about Replay Tests on the wiki](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/Replay-Tests).\n* [Check the example test code](https://github.com/Terasology/TestReplayModule/blob/master/src/test/java/org/terasology/replayTests/CuttingGrassBlockPositionReplayTest.java) to understand how to get the block type from the game.\n\n# See also\n\n* [The Record and Replay Wiki](https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/How-to-Use-Record-and-Replay).\n* [Another example test code](https://github.com/Terasology/TestReplayModule/blob/master/src/test/java/org/terasology/replayTests/WoodCutReplayTest.java).',NULL,0,'Replay Test: Breaking stones',1912830,'https://trello.com/c/7KFP7ftT','5b9b100cca1728134ee88b15','5da6ffb280d00419145f796a'),('5bcd69a30b52191d1071f3ec',NULL,1,'2020-09-13 00:02:05.146482','2018-10-23 16:32:00.775000','2020-09-13 00:02:05.146483','{emoji={}}','# Make a silly new UI screen\n\nUI is a vitally important element of \n\nAll the UI in Terasology is done using [our own system called NUI](). \n\n# Definition of \'Done\'\n\n* Put bullet points here for the final state that\'ll satisfy the task\n* Include at least one \"deliverable\" - usually a screenshot for any task involving game assets (forces testing of the game - if it doesn\'t work yet then the task isn\'t done yet, ask for help!), a forum thread or wiki page for a document, a youtube link for a video, and so on\n\n# Where to start\n\n* More bullet points! Give the student instructions for the starting state to aim for (working workspace etc)\n* Give names of classes or other code resources to search for, if applicable\n* Link to related information to investigate\n\n# See also\n\n* Put a link here to a section on https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/wiki/GCI if there is one describing this specific cat